{{ 'dspln-artwork-page.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}

<section class="dspln-artwork dspln-artwork-guide" aria-label="Detailed artwork guidelines">
  <div class="dspln-artwork-guide__inner">
    <div class="dspln-artwork-guide__block">
      <figure class="dspln-artwork-guide__image">
        <img src="{{ 'dspln-artwork-file-icon.avif' | asset_url }}" alt="" width="480" height="480" loading="lazy">
      </figure>
      <h3>File Format</h3>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Preferred Formats:</strong> PNG files provide the best results as PNGs support transparent backgrounds, so you won't have unwanted color and space around your design.</li>
        <li><strong>Alternative Formats:</strong> If PNG files are not available, high-resolution raster files in formats like JPEG, GIF or TIFF are also acceptable. Ensure that raster files have a resolution of at least 300 DPI for optimal embroidery quality. We'll review and edit your file before sending it to you for approval.</li>
        <li><strong>File Size:</strong> 4MB is the max size you can upload for each logo. The maximum upload size for each logo is 4MB. If your file exceeds this limit and you're unable to upload it, please consider reducing the DPI (dots per inch) or overall measurements of the artwork but do not reduce it less than 4" wide or in height.</li>
        <li><strong>Don't Worry:</strong> I will personally review each of your files to ensure they meet our quality standards. If adjustments are needed, I'll reach out to inform you. Once I've confirmed your desired results, I'll make the necessary edits. You'll then have the chance to approve the edited version before production begins.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="dspln-artwork-guide__block">
      <figure class="dspln-artwork-guide__image">
        <img src="{{ 'dspln-artwork-back-logo.avif' | asset_url }}" alt="" width="480" height="480" loading="lazy">
      </figure>
      <h3>Size and Placement</h3>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Artwork Measurements:</strong> In general, larger artwork measurements result in better quality, especially when they're reduced. Our customizer app automatically reduces your artwork size to 4" wide in all logo areas except the back of the kimono.</li>
        <li><strong>Embroidery on back of kimono:</strong> For the back of the kimono, where embroidery is 10" wide, we recommend keeping the artwork at least 10" wide for optimal results. Keep in mind that smaller details may not translate well in embroidery, so simplify intricate designs if necessary.</li>
        <li><strong>Don't Worry:</strong> I will individually review and edit each of your artworks to ensure they meet our standards for the best results. You'll have the opportunity to approve the edited version before production begins.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="dspln-artwork-guide__block">
      <figure class="dspln-artwork-guide__image">
        <img src="{{ 'dspln-artwork-logo-stitch.avif' | asset_url }}" alt="" width="480" height="480" loading="lazy">
      </figure>
      <h3>Color and Stitching</h3>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Thread Colors:</strong> We'll utilize standard colors that closely match yours. However, if you have a specific shade in mind, please provide the corresponding Pantone number. Our embroidery machines can recreate a wide range of colors, but it's essential to choose colors that complement your design and garment.</li>
        <li><strong>Stitch Types:</strong> Smaller areas like letters will be directly embroidered with thread. For larger spaces, we'll use fabric applique, which involves stitching fabric down to fill the area and then securing it along the edges with embroidery. Appliques will be mostly utilized for the bigger back logo. Smaller areas like letters will be directly embroidered with thread.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="dspln-artwork-guide__block">
      <figure class="dspln-artwork-guide__image">
        <img src="{{ 'dspln-artwork-embroidered-d.webp' | asset_url }}" alt="" width="480" height="480" loading="lazy">
      </figure>
      <h3>Design and Detail</h3>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Simplification:</strong> Simplify complex designs by reducing the number of colors and fine details. Embroidery works best with bold, distinct elements that can be easily replicated with thread.</li>
        <li><strong>Text Considerations:</strong> If your design includes text, use clear and legible fonts. Thin or intricate fonts may not embroider well.</li>
        <li><strong>Thickness and Density:</strong> Maintain a balance between the thickness and density of your embroidery. Dense stitching can cause the fabric to pucker, while overly thin stitching may not be visible enough.</li>
        <li>Small Avoid using very small letters because the embroidered text might not be legible. Keep the text at least 0.25" in height and at least 0.05" thick.</li>
        <li>The minimum recommended line thickness for the regular satin stitch is 0.05". For thinner lines we'll use run stitch (a single line of stitches). You can measure the text in Illustrator either by using the measuring tool, or by converting the font point size to inches or centimeters. You can do this by going to: File &gt; Preferences &gt; Units &gt; General &gt; Inches or CM. 0.25" is equivalent to approximately 36pt, and the letters will also have the necessary thickness. But this depends on the font. We recommend using simple fonts like Arial, Helvetica, Myriad pro.</li>
        <li>Photographic images: It's impossible to embroider photographic images. Also neon and metallic colors dont render well either.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="dspln-artwork-guide__block">
      <figure class="dspln-artwork-guide__image">
        <img src="{{ 'dspln-artwork-sewing.avif' | asset_url }}" alt="" width="480" height="480" loading="lazy">
      </figure>
      <h3>Design Service</h3>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Canva:</strong> There are fantastic websites available that don't require any prior design or software knowledge. The most popular one is Canva. Additionally, there are amazing AI-powered platforms where you can generate artwork effortlessly.</li>
        <li><strong>In House Graphic Design:</strong> We offer a wide range of graphic design services, including logos and artwork tailored to your needs. Feel free to contact us, and I'll be happy to provide you with a price quote.</li>
        <li><strong>Specialized Custom Gi Design:</strong> We handcraft all our gis, allowing us to customize every single element. If you desire additional customization beyond what is available on our website, please reach out to us, and we'll be happy to accommodate your needs.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="dspln-artwork-guide__block">
      <h3>Additional Notes</h3>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Proofing:</strong> Before finalizing your order, we'll provide a digital proof of your embroidery design for your approval. Review the proof carefully to ensure that your artwork appears as intended.</li>
        <li><strong>Custom Requests:</strong> If you have any specific requests or instructions regarding your embroidery, please include them when submitting your order. We're here to accommodate your unique preferences and requirements.</li>
      </ol>
      <figure class="dspln-artwork-guide__wide">
        <img src="{{ 'dspln-artwork-fist-bump.webp' | asset_url }}" alt="" width="1024" height="300" loading="lazy">
      </figure>
    </div>

    <div class="dspln-artwork-guide__conclusion">
      <h3>Conclusion</h3>
      <p>By adhering to these artwork guidelines, you'll help us create a custom gi that meets your expectations and showcases your individuality. If you have any questions or need further assistance, please don't hesitate to contact us. We're excited to bring your vision to life!</p>
      <figure class="dspln-artwork-guide__logo">
        <img src="{{ 'dspln-artwork-foot-logo.avif' | asset_url }}" alt="DSPLN" width="480" height="480" loading="lazy">
      </figure>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

